headline: Delta Air Lines (DAL) Profit Margins Slip Below Prior Year, Reinforcing Cautious Growth Narrative
summary: Delta Air Lines (DAL) posted net profit margins of 7.4%, just off last year’s 7.7% mark, and continued its profitability streak from the past five years with an impressive 73.2% annual earnings growth over that period. Despite high-quality earnings, the outlook is more cautious. Revenue is forecast to grow just 2.8% per year compared to the US market’s 10%, and earnings are expected to fall by 7.1% a year for the next three years. headline: DAL Q3 Deep Dive: Premium, Corporate and Loyalty Segments Power Delta’s Revenue Growth
summary: Global airline Delta Air Lines (NYSE:DAL) reported Q3 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 6.4% year on year to $16.67 billion. Guidance for next quarter’s revenue was optimistic at $16.03 billion at the midpoint, 2.2% above analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $2.17 per share was 39.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

Its GAAP profit of $2.17 per share was 39.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
